WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:29.320 --> 00:00:30.864
Cordon the area.

3
00:00:33.616 --> 00:00:35.993
Mike! What do you think happened?

4
00:00:35.994 --> 00:00:40.457
Hard to say. All we really know
is somebody shot Calvin.

5
00:00:41.833 --> 00:00:44.001
You don't seriously think
it was Charmaine?

6
00:00:44.002 --> 00:00:45.919
I mean. he was a career criminal.

7
00:00:45.920 --> 00:00:47.756
He <i>was</i> in the twins' room.

8
00:00:48.339 --> 00:00:50.841
- You think they're okay?
- Yeah. they're okay.

9
00:00:50.842 --> 00:00:53.594
We just got some CCTV footage
of her and the boys

10
00:00:53.595 --> 00:00:55.554
at a gas station a couple hours away.

11
00:00:55.555 --> 00:00:58.058
so they're safe.
but they're clearly on the run.

12
00:00:58.641 --> 00:01:00.976
Well. look. if there's anything I can do…

13
00:01:00.977 --> 00:01:05.523
You can be honest with me…
and let me know if she reaches out.

14
00:01:06.024 --> 00:01:07.609
Why wouldn't I be honest with you?

15
00:01:08.193 --> 00:01:09.402
I don't know.

16
00:01:10.695 --> 00:01:11.738
Hey. man. you okay?

17
00:01:13.239 --> 00:01:16.450
Yeah. Just…tell me if you hear
from Charmaine. okay?

18
00:01:16.451 --> 00:01:17.702
I gotta go back in.

19
00:01:29.464 --> 00:01:32.217
I've left her a bunch of messages.
She's not responding.

20
00:01:33.134 --> 00:01:35.844
I'm so worried about her.
She must be so scared.

21
00:01:35.845 --> 00:01:37.722
Yeah. I mean. I'm worried too.

22
00:01:38.723 --> 00:01:39.890
But…

23
00:01:39.891 --> 00:01:43.061
at least we know the person
who's most likely to harm her

24
00:01:43.645 --> 00:01:45.646
is out of the picture now.

25
00:01:45.647 --> 00:01:46.648
Yeah.

26
00:01:47.607 --> 00:01:48.608
That's true.

27
00:01:49.109 --> 00:01:49.984
Oh!

28
00:01:50.485 --> 00:01:52.611
- What?
- I forgot your food.

29
00:01:52.612 --> 00:01:54.656
- Oh. It's okay.
- Sorry.

30
00:01:55.156 --> 00:01:56.448
You had your hands full.

31
00:01:56.449 --> 00:01:57.741
Mm…

32
00:01:57.742 --> 00:01:58.909
How was your morning?

33
00:01:58.910 --> 00:02:01.745
Well. this morning after you left.
my patient Marley

34
00:02:01.746 --> 00:02:06.709
showed up here. um. in a panic. and. uh…

35
00:02:08.461 --> 00:02:10.547
she offered us her baby.

36
00:02:11.131 --> 00:02:13.382
I thought she'd already
found parents to adopt.

37
00:02:13.383 --> 00:02:17.971
Yes. she had. but the couple she chose
ended up fighting and backing out.

38
00:02:19.264 --> 00:02:20.890
- Wow!
- Yeah.

39
00:02:21.724 --> 00:02:22.933
So what'd you say?

40
00:02:22.934 --> 00:02:24.977
I mean. I told her
she needed to get some rest

41
00:02:24.978 --> 00:02:26.478
and not to make a rash decision.

42
00:02:26.479 --> 00:02:31.191
Sure. but you wanted to say yes
because we want a baby. right?

43
00:02:31.192 --> 00:02:33.861
- We do.
- Of course.
That's a thing. but we've…

44
00:02:33.862 --> 00:02:34.945
Jack. come on.

45
00:02:34.946 --> 00:02:38.283
We've been through so much
to have one. and this just… It feels…

46
00:02:39.075 --> 00:02:40.368
just too…

47
00:02:40.869 --> 00:02:42.035
Too easy?

48
00:02:42.036 --> 00:02:43.997
And unstable.

49
00:02:44.622 --> 00:02:47.207
Honestly. I mean.
I don't think she thought it through…

50
00:02:47.208 --> 00:02:48.375
at all. you know?

51
00:02:48.376 --> 00:02:51.170
She was really upset. She was desperate.

52
00:02:51.171 --> 00:02:53.089
And she doesn't even know us.

53
00:02:55.091 --> 00:02:56.300
Okay.

54
00:02:56.301 --> 00:02:57.467
Yeah.

55
00:02:57.468 --> 00:02:59.720
Yeah. no. I get it.
I mean. there's no rush.

56
00:02:59.721 --> 00:03:01.430
- Yeah.
- Okay.

57
00:03:01.431 --> 00:03:05.142
We'll just keep working with the adoption
agency to find the right match.

58
00:03:05.143 --> 00:03:06.811
- Yeah.
- Plus. that'll…

59
00:03:07.979 --> 00:03:12.149
give us some time to…
focus on being newlyweds. right?

60
00:03:12.150 --> 00:03:12.984
Yeah.

61
00:03:13.484 --> 00:03:15.360
Which I'm very much looking forward to.

62
00:03:15.361 --> 00:03:16.528
So am I.

63
00:03:16.529 --> 00:03:18.739
Good. Then get dressed.

64
00:03:18.740 --> 00:03:20.158
- Wait!
- I got a surprise.

65
00:03:21.701 --> 00:03:22.535
But…

66
00:03:25.914 --> 00:03:27.497
I planned this months ago

67
00:03:27.498 --> 00:03:30.250
when I realized we couldn't go
on our honeymoon right away.

68
00:03:30.251 --> 00:03:33.545
Ah. well. I have some thoughts
on where we should go.

69
00:03:33.546 --> 00:03:35.672
- Oh! You do?
- When we go there. Yes. I do.

70
00:03:35.673 --> 00:03:37.257
- Well. so do I. actually.
- Really?

71
00:03:37.258 --> 00:03:39.801
Yeah. maybe we should say
what we're both thinking on three.

72
00:03:39.802 --> 00:03:40.761
- Okay.
- You ready?

73
00:03:40.762 --> 00:03:42.638
- Yep. Mmm-hmm.
- One.

74
00:03:42.639 --> 00:03:44.056
- Two. Three.
- Mmm-hmm.

75
00:03:44.057 --> 00:03:45.724
- Hawaii.
- Italy!

76
00:03:45.725 --> 00:03:46.808
- Oh wow.
- Oh no.

77
00:03:46.809 --> 00:03:48.644
- Those are so not the same place.
- No!

78
00:03:48.645 --> 00:03:50.729
Well. I was thinking
someplace. like. beachy.

79
00:03:50.730 --> 00:03:52.898
- Hawaii?
- Clothing optional.

80
00:03:52.899 --> 00:03:56.360
Well. I get it. but I was thinking.
you know. romantic. old-world cities.

81
00:03:56.361 --> 00:03:57.903
Clothing also optional.

82
00:03:57.904 --> 00:04:00.864
All right. That's…
You're gonna have to convince me. though.

83
00:04:00.865 --> 00:04:03.409
Oh. challenge accepted.

84
00:04:03.993 --> 00:04:06.955
But. before we pick
our honeymoon destination…

85
00:04:07.455 --> 00:04:08.539
we're here.

86
00:04:09.040 --> 00:04:11.793
What is this?

87
00:04:12.669 --> 00:04:15.088
Just a reminder
that there's no place like home.

88
00:04:16.381 --> 00:04:19.049
I mean. come on. we had to do
something epic to celebrate.

89
00:04:19.050 --> 00:04:22.803
But we just got married. Yesterday. What…

90
00:04:22.804 --> 00:04:25.389
What else could we
possibly be celebrating?

91
00:04:25.390 --> 00:04:28.476
- The first day of the rest of our lives.
- Aww.

92
00:04:29.143 --> 00:04:31.812
- We couldn't do that on the ground?
- Nope!

93
00:04:33.648 --> 00:04:34.982
- Oh my God.
- Yes!

94
00:04:34.983 --> 00:04:36.108
No!

95
00:04:48.871 --> 00:04:51.666
<i>♪ If I get too close ♪</i>

96
00:04:52.875 --> 00:04:55.628
<i>♪ And I'm not how you hoped ♪</i>

97
00:04:56.921 --> 00:04:59.881
<i>♪ Forgive my northern attitude ♪</i>

98
00:04:59.882 --> 00:05:03.344
<i>♪ Oh. I was raised out in the cold ♪</i>

99
00:05:04.846 --> 00:05:07.307
<i>♪ If the sun don't rise ♪</i>

100
00:05:08.599 --> 00:05:11.102
<i>♪ Till the summertime ♪</i>

101
00:05:12.395 --> 00:05:15.439
<i>♪ Forgive my northern attitude ♪</i>

102
00:05:15.440 --> 00:05:19.193
<i>♪ Oh. I was raised on little light ♪</i>

103
00:05:29.412 --> 00:05:32.372
So what does a state medical board
investigation consist of?

104
00:05:32.373 --> 00:05:34.291
Well. mostly bullshit.

105
00:05:34.292 --> 00:05:37.669
- Doc Mullins!
- Hey. I just… Sue me. I'm pissed.

106
00:05:37.670 --> 00:05:39.254
I know. honey. We all are.

107
00:05:39.255 --> 00:05:40.964
Hey.

108
00:05:40.965 --> 00:05:42.049
Sorry I'm late.

109
00:05:42.050 --> 00:05:44.551
Oh. don't apologize. Mel.
I'm sorry you had to come in.

110
00:05:44.552 --> 00:05:47.721
I mean. you should be
basking in the afterglow of your wedding.

111
00:05:47.722 --> 00:05:50.182
Well. I am. But I'm happy to be here now.

112
00:05:50.183 --> 00:05:52.142
Uh. what did I miss?

113
00:05:52.143 --> 00:05:56.063
So. this board will be looking
at the events surrounding the house call

114
00:05:56.064 --> 00:05:58.523
that saved Henry's life.

115
00:05:58.524 --> 00:06:00.692
But how they do it. it's up to them.

116
00:06:00.693 --> 00:06:03.403
And we have no idea
how long it's gonna take.

117
00:06:03.404 --> 00:06:05.489
In the meantime.
you can't see any patients at all?

118
00:06:05.490 --> 00:06:08.700
We looked into an emergency hearing
to see if we could speed this up.

119
00:06:08.701 --> 00:06:12.245
Yeah. my lawyer said. "No. we won't have
enough time to prepare your defense

120
00:06:12.246 --> 00:06:14.331
if we force the medical board's hand."

121
00:06:14.332 --> 00:06:16.958
I don't understand
why Grace Valley is coming after you

122
00:06:16.959 --> 00:06:18.835
for saving a man's life.

123
00:06:18.836 --> 00:06:20.504
Hope and I did a little digging.

124
00:06:20.505 --> 00:06:22.631
Turns out that quack. Dr. Hayes.

125
00:06:22.632 --> 00:06:26.468
is using this to expand the Grace Valley
network into Virgin River.

126
00:06:26.469 --> 00:06:29.388
Which is why they're trying
to get you out of the picture.

127
00:06:29.389 --> 00:06:30.306
Yep.

128
00:06:32.141 --> 00:06:33.184
How can we help?

129
00:06:33.935 --> 00:06:39.147
Well. first. you can focus
on your treatment and getting better.

130
00:06:39.148 --> 00:06:42.234
And we're gonna see what I can do
on a civic level to stop this.

131
00:06:42.235 --> 00:06:44.694
Thank you. Mel. uh…

132
00:06:44.695 --> 00:06:46.947
I'm gonna need you
to cover for me with our patients.

133
00:06:46.948 --> 00:06:48.949
You don't think
we should bring in another doctor?

134
00:06:48.950 --> 00:06:52.035
No. No. you're licensed
to do the majority of what I do here

135
00:06:52.036 --> 00:06:53.454
on a day-to-day basis.

136
00:06:54.455 --> 00:06:57.499
Plus. no one I trust
more than you to do it.

137
00:06:57.500 --> 00:06:59.960
Thank you. That means a lot.

138
00:06:59.961 --> 00:07:03.422
Look. I have a consult
with Marley in a few.

139
00:07:03.423 --> 00:07:06.258
so can we go over the rest of this after?

140
00:07:06.259 --> 00:07:08.386
- Yeah. Okay.
- Yeah. I'm gonna go.

141
00:07:08.886 --> 00:07:10.096
Thanks.

142
00:07:18.646 --> 00:07:25.194
<i>♪ When the moon hits your eye
Like a big pizza pie. that's amore ♪</i>

143
00:07:26.362 --> 00:07:29.948
Thank you for this awesome oven.
This is perfect.

144
00:07:29.949 --> 00:07:33.577
I convinced Mel we should go to Italy.

145
00:07:33.578 --> 00:07:35.745
Why does she need convincing?

146
00:07:35.746 --> 00:07:37.581
She wants to just lay on a beach.

147
00:07:37.582 --> 00:07:40.792
I want our honeymoon
to be an epic romantic adventure!

148
00:07:40.793 --> 00:07:41.960
Of course you do.

149
00:07:41.961 --> 00:07:44.754
That is very on-brand for Jack Sheridan.

150
00:07:44.755 --> 00:07:46.923
I mean. you built the woman
her dream home already.

151
00:07:46.924 --> 00:07:48.216
It's not done yet.

152
00:07:48.217 --> 00:07:49.468
Uh…

153
00:07:49.469 --> 00:07:51.761
- Oh.
- This isn't done either.

154
00:07:51.762 --> 00:07:53.430
- Chef.
- You want me to try again?

155
00:07:53.431 --> 00:07:54.514
- Yes.
- You got time?

156
00:07:54.515 --> 00:07:55.640
- Oh. I do.
- Okay.

157
00:07:57.310 --> 00:07:59.645
This distraction is helping.

158
00:08:00.646 --> 00:08:02.315
Distraction? From what?

159
00:08:04.400 --> 00:08:07.153
Mike figured out
what happened with me and Brady.

160
00:08:08.404 --> 00:08:09.696
Ooh.

161
00:08:09.697 --> 00:08:11.239
Well. how'd he find out?

162
00:08:11.240 --> 00:08:14.910
I don't know.
I felt so guilty. I was too afraid to ask.

163
00:08:14.911 --> 00:08:18.664
Maybe that's why he was…
a little weird with me yesterday.

164
00:08:19.582 --> 00:08:21.374
- So did he end it?
- No.

165
00:08:21.375 --> 00:08:22.919
He proposed.

166
00:08:24.295 --> 00:08:25.296
What?

167
00:08:25.796 --> 00:08:30.634
Yeah. he said he could forgive me
if I just chose him once and for all.

168
00:08:30.635 --> 00:08:34.263
But I don't know.
It felt like some sort of quid pro quo.

169
00:08:35.640 --> 00:08:38.683
- Yeah. but that doesn't sound like Mike.
- No. I know.

170
00:08:38.684 --> 00:08:43.688
And I think he was just saying. you know.
he would love me no matter what

171
00:08:43.689 --> 00:08:48.486
if I could just commit
to loving him the same way.

172
00:08:50.404 --> 00:08:53.615
I want to.
I just told him I needed time to think.

173
00:08:53.616 --> 00:08:54.909
Take it.

174
00:08:56.035 --> 00:08:59.496
It's a huge decision.
I mean. even under normal circumstances.

175
00:08:59.497 --> 00:09:01.998
Is that your sage advice
for your little sis?

176
00:09:01.999 --> 00:09:04.919
I'm just saying. I want you to have
everything that you want.

177
00:09:05.461 --> 00:09:08.046
Everything that you dream of.
just like I have with Mel.

178
00:09:10.466 --> 00:09:12.426
Just gotta figure out what that is.

179
00:09:20.476 --> 00:09:21.851
Mike! Hey!

180
00:09:21.852 --> 00:09:24.062
- Can we chat?
- You look like crap.

181
00:09:24.063 --> 00:09:27.524
Yeah. well. I haven't really slept.
Lark. she cleared me out.

182
00:09:27.525 --> 00:09:30.151
Took every cent I had and skipped town.

183
00:09:30.152 --> 00:09:31.361
You should call your bank.

184
00:09:31.362 --> 00:09:34.781
Yeah. I did. but they said because
she used my login to transfer the money.

185
00:09:34.782 --> 00:09:36.032
insurance won't cover it.

186
00:09:36.033 --> 00:09:37.409
Said to file a police report.

187
00:09:37.410 --> 00:09:40.328
By the time you guys find her.
the money will be long gone. Look…

188
00:09:40.329 --> 00:09:42.122
I could really use your help.

189
00:09:42.123 --> 00:09:43.790
Calvin's dead. Charmaine's missing.

190
00:09:43.791 --> 00:09:47.335
I'm a little busy right now.
so your money is your problem. okay?

191
00:09:47.336 --> 00:09:49.130
Come on. can't you do me a favor?

192
00:09:50.381 --> 00:09:52.091
I'm not lifting a finger for you.

193
00:09:52.717 --> 00:09:54.010
Actually. that's a lie.

194
00:09:57.555 --> 00:09:59.265
That's for sleeping with Brie.

195
00:10:05.771 --> 00:10:09.190
Marley. I know that you are going
to find the right parents for your baby.

196
00:10:09.191 --> 00:10:10.735
Yeah. I hope you're right.

197
00:10:11.235 --> 00:10:13.361
I'm so sorry
about coming to your house like that.

198
00:10:13.362 --> 00:10:17.157
- It was crazy.
- No. no. no. it was not crazy. It was--

199
00:10:17.158 --> 00:10:20.243
- A little crazy.
- No. it was completely understandable.

200
00:10:20.244 --> 00:10:23.204
Phil and Darla have put you
in an impossible situation.

201
00:10:23.205 --> 00:10:25.082
Yeah. I'm a mess.

202
00:10:29.086 --> 00:10:31.171
I just want to find a good home for him.

203
00:10:31.172 --> 00:10:33.757
I know. I know you do.

204
00:10:33.758 --> 00:10:37.969
And. look. I am sure that there are
a lot of prospective parents

205
00:10:37.970 --> 00:10:40.305
who are open to last-minute situations.

206
00:10:40.306 --> 00:10:41.682
I know. It just…

207
00:10:42.266 --> 00:10:43.892
It won't be in Virgin River.

208
00:10:43.893 --> 00:10:46.646
Well. you don't… you don't know that.

209
00:10:47.146 --> 00:10:49.773
Regardless. you're…
you're gonna have good options.

210
00:10:49.774 --> 00:10:52.985
I'm just not sure I can trust myself
to pick the right ones.

211
00:10:53.944 --> 00:10:57.072
My taste in adoptive parents
is almost as bad as my taste in men.

212
00:10:57.073 --> 00:11:01.619
Look. don't beat yourself up. okay?
You are only 22 years old.

213
00:11:02.536 --> 00:11:04.954
Seriously. I feel like
dating the wrong men

214
00:11:04.955 --> 00:11:07.457
is just. like. a part of growing up.

215
00:11:07.458 --> 00:11:13.213
When I was your age.
I dated a saxophonist in a ska band.

216
00:11:13.214 --> 00:11:15.882
- Oh! Okay! Mmm-hmm.
- Yeah.

217
00:11:15.883 --> 00:11:18.635
Then I fell in love
with this arrogant doctor

218
00:11:18.636 --> 00:11:21.012
while I was in Malaysia
doing Nurses Beyond Borders.

219
00:11:21.013 --> 00:11:22.555
I mean. this guy was…

220
00:11:22.556 --> 00:11:24.265
He was a piece of work.

221
00:11:24.266 --> 00:11:27.561
But he was the reason I became a midwife.

222
00:11:29.021 --> 00:11:31.564
I just think sometimes
when you're on the wrong path.

223
00:11:31.565 --> 00:11:34.026
it leads you
to where you're supposed to be.

224
00:11:36.862 --> 00:11:38.697
You're very wise. Mel.

225
00:11:38.698 --> 00:11:40.281
Oh. please.

226
00:11:40.282 --> 00:11:43.952
And since you are. do you think you could
look at parent profiles with me later?

227
00:11:43.953 --> 00:11:45.912
Just as a second set of eyes?

228
00:11:45.913 --> 00:11:47.623
I would be honored.

229
00:11:48.124 --> 00:11:49.709
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

230
00:11:50.710 --> 00:11:53.086
So do you think
you're gonna stay with Phil and Darla?

231
00:11:53.087 --> 00:11:54.796
- No!
- Okay.

232
00:11:54.797 --> 00:11:57.841
- Uh. they are putting me up at the B&B.
- Okay.

233
00:11:57.842 --> 00:12:01.345
I do feel a little guilty 'cause money was
one of the things they were fighting over.

234
00:12:03.013 --> 00:12:08.102
You know what? Actually. I think I might
have a place you can stay rent-free.

235
00:12:17.486 --> 00:12:18.487
Hey. Roland!

236
00:12:20.865 --> 00:12:24.284
Easy. buddy. Hey. Roland.
what the hell do you think you're doing?

237
00:12:24.285 --> 00:12:25.745
Calling in a favor.

238
00:12:26.579 --> 00:12:28.205
Well. I didn't know I owed you any.

239
00:12:28.873 --> 00:12:32.542
After what you pulled with Sugar?
You owe me several.

240
00:12:32.543 --> 00:12:34.711
Look.
if you want your gas money back…

241
00:12:34.712 --> 00:12:37.297
Nah. Look. I got a couple
of new thoroughbreds.

242
00:12:37.298 --> 00:12:39.174
I don't have room for these old horses.

243
00:12:39.175 --> 00:12:43.219
I didn't want to euthanize them.
and you got land out here for days.

244
00:12:43.220 --> 00:12:45.263
You know. you could do a lot with it.

245
00:12:45.264 --> 00:12:48.601
Are you serious? Roland. I don't
even know what I'm doing with Sugar here.

246
00:12:49.393 --> 00:12:52.479
Tell you what. why don't you sleep on it?

247
00:12:52.480 --> 00:12:55.483
You decide you still don't want 'em
in the morning. give me a call.

248
00:12:56.150 --> 00:12:58.276
I'll swing by with my shotgun.

249
00:13:13.584 --> 00:13:15.877
Oh!

250
00:13:15.878 --> 00:13:19.756
Well. I gotta say. Mel and Jack's wedding
was more fun than I had expected.

251
00:13:19.757 --> 00:13:22.300
Especially that photo booth.

252
00:13:22.301 --> 00:13:25.345
What happened in that photo booth
stays in that photo booth.

253
00:13:25.346 --> 00:13:29.099
Yes. unless I somehow happen
to get a small strip of pictures of it.

254
00:13:29.725 --> 00:13:31.476
Ooh!

255
00:13:31.477 --> 00:13:33.228
You did not.

256
00:13:33.229 --> 00:13:38.609
I did not. but I do have
a lot of mental images.

257
00:13:41.487 --> 00:13:44.113
So. I guess we just seat ourselves?

258
00:13:44.114 --> 00:13:47.535
Hey. folks. take a seat wherever you like.
I'll be right with you.

259
00:13:49.453 --> 00:13:52.038
So. you gotta work tonight?

260
00:13:52.039 --> 00:13:55.334
I doubt it.
Kind of a slow start to fire season.

261
00:13:55.960 --> 00:13:59.212
Which. as a private citizen.
I am very grateful for.

262
00:13:59.213 --> 00:14:02.131
but as a firefighter.
I am getting stir-crazy.

263
00:14:02.132 --> 00:14:05.260
- Mmm.
- Without a fire to fight. who am I?

264
00:14:05.261 --> 00:14:06.511
I don't know!

265
00:14:06.512 --> 00:14:08.263
Sexy pool shark?

266
00:14:08.264 --> 00:14:10.223
Oh! I'll take it.

267
00:14:10.224 --> 00:14:11.684
Uh. excuse me.

268
00:14:12.476 --> 00:14:15.229
I don't see your buttermilk pork chop
on the menu.

269
00:14:16.564 --> 00:14:19.859
That's 'cause that dish
was never on the menu.

270
00:14:20.734 --> 00:14:23.611
Seriously? We drove all the way
from Arcata to try it.

271
00:14:23.612 --> 00:14:26.823
Yeah. um. and according
to <i>Food & Wine</i> magazine.

272
00:14:26.824 --> 00:14:28.409
it's the best pork chop in the state.

273
00:14:30.286 --> 00:14:32.162
<i>Food & Wine!</i>

274
00:14:32.705 --> 00:14:35.832
John. this is huge.
Why didn't you tell me?

275
00:14:35.833 --> 00:14:39.335
I… I didn't know. Otherwise.
I would have added it to the menu.

276
00:14:39.336 --> 00:14:40.795
How did this happen?

277
00:14:40.796 --> 00:14:42.965
My friend Jamie. she… she writes for them.

278
00:14:43.465 --> 00:14:44.841
And she stopped in.

279
00:14:44.842 --> 00:14:47.719
so I had her taste-test some dishes
for the rehearsal dinner.

280
00:14:47.720 --> 00:14:50.972
As much as I love
hearing the article's origin story.

281
00:14:50.973 --> 00:14:51.974
we're starving.

282
00:14:52.808 --> 00:14:54.767
Hey. listen.
seeing as you drove all this way.

283
00:14:54.768 --> 00:14:57.395
why don't I whip you up
something special? Yeah?

284
00:14:57.396 --> 00:15:00.315
Yeah? And drinks are on the house.

285
00:15:00.316 --> 00:15:02.151
I do love a White Claw.

286
00:15:02.735 --> 00:15:04.194
I bet you do.

287
00:15:05.529 --> 00:15:09.366
Hey. Hannah. would you mind
helping out these. uh. nice folks?

288
00:15:09.950 --> 00:15:11.284
- Yeah!
- Yeah. Okay.

289
00:15:11.285 --> 00:15:12.536
Hey.

290
00:15:13.454 --> 00:15:16.956
We need to celebrate!
I'm gonna do something special for you.

291
00:15:16.957 --> 00:15:19.250
- Oh no. you don't have to do that.
- Well. I know.

292
00:15:19.251 --> 00:15:21.420
It wouldn't be very special
if I <i>had</i> to do it.

293
00:15:23.172 --> 00:15:24.923
Now get in that kitchen.

294
00:15:24.924 --> 00:15:27.091
You've got work to do. chef.

295
00:15:27.092 --> 00:15:28.010
You.

296
00:15:29.011 --> 00:15:30.845
Hey. babe. I'm not sure what you're up to.

297
00:15:30.846 --> 00:15:34.182
but I just wanted to let you know
that I told my patient

298
00:15:34.183 --> 00:15:38.102
I will not be adopting… her baby.

299
00:15:38.103 --> 00:15:41.689
I did. however. offer her the Airstream.

300
00:15:41.690 --> 00:15:43.191
I hope that's okay with you.

301
00:15:43.192 --> 00:15:46.487
Uh. anyway. I'll talk to you later.
Love you. Bye.

302
00:15:48.322 --> 00:15:49.572
Hi. there!

303
00:15:49.573 --> 00:15:52.617
Do you typically consider
adopting your patients' babies?

304
00:15:52.618 --> 00:15:55.036
You know what?
I find that working in rural medicine.

305
00:15:55.037 --> 00:15:56.705
there's really no such thing as typical.

306
00:15:57.957 --> 00:16:01.459
Uh. anyway. I'm Mel.
What brings you to the clinic today?

307
00:16:01.460 --> 00:16:02.919
The state medical board.

308
00:16:02.920 --> 00:16:04.879
My name is Victoria Ellis.

309
00:16:04.880 --> 00:16:05.880
Oh.

310
00:16:05.881 --> 00:16:08.132
I was hired
to conduct a formal investigation

311
00:16:08.133 --> 00:16:10.760
into the case against Dr. Vernon Mullins.

312
00:16:10.761 --> 00:16:13.388
I take it you're his nurse.
Melinda Monroe?

313
00:16:13.389 --> 00:16:15.139
Uh. yeah. Uh. Sheridan.

314
00:16:15.140 --> 00:16:17.016
I'm going to need interviews
with clinic staff

315
00:16:17.017 --> 00:16:19.644
as well as anyone involved in the incident
as part of my report.

316
00:16:19.645 --> 00:16:23.398
which will help the board determine
whether they take this complaint to trial.

317
00:16:23.399 --> 00:16:26.610
- Right.
- Oh. everyone'll be happy to talk to you.

318
00:16:27.236 --> 00:16:30.113
Including Henry. and Henry's son Cody.

319
00:16:30.114 --> 00:16:32.700
who was there
the day I saved his father's life.

320
00:16:33.200 --> 00:16:36.035
And we have
absolutely nothing to hide from you.

321
00:16:36.036 --> 00:16:37.870
And I'm Dr. Vernon Mullins.

322
00:16:37.871 --> 00:16:40.832
I don't do handshakes. Nothing personal.

323
00:16:40.833 --> 00:16:41.959
I'm a germophobe.

324
00:16:42.751 --> 00:16:45.044
Odd line of work you picked then. huh?

325
00:16:45.045 --> 00:16:47.171
I didn't pick the medical field.

326
00:16:47.172 --> 00:16:49.341
I was a detective. I got shot.

327
00:16:49.925 --> 00:16:53.386
I wanted to keep investigating.
but reduce my risk of getting shot.

328
00:16:53.387 --> 00:16:56.055
Do you have a private office
I could use to conduct interviews?

329
00:16:56.056 --> 00:16:59.267
- I have the only private office.
- Perfect. You won't have use for it.

330
00:16:59.268 --> 00:17:02.895
Now. wait. just because I can't practice
medicine doesn't mean that I won't be--

331
00:17:02.896 --> 00:17:05.356
Cooperative. right?

332
00:17:05.357 --> 00:17:08.027
Because we do need
to get you back to practicing.

333
00:17:08.652 --> 00:17:10.278
- Yes.
- Yes.

334
00:17:10.279 --> 00:17:12.531
- Yes. we do.
- Great. Then it's settled.

335
00:17:13.115 --> 00:17:15.284
- I'll show you the way.
- Thank you.

336
00:17:29.131 --> 00:17:31.758
Whoa! What happened to you?

337
00:17:31.759 --> 00:17:34.844
- Mike found out I slept with Brie.
- Ah! Could have been worse. then.

338
00:17:34.845 --> 00:17:37.889
Oh. it is.
Lark stole all my money. disappeared.

339
00:17:37.890 --> 00:17:40.225
and now I'm on my own to get it back.

340
00:17:41.060 --> 00:17:43.936
Oh my God. I'm so sorry.

341
00:17:43.937 --> 00:17:45.855
- I think I need some ice.
- Good idea.

342
00:17:45.856 --> 00:17:47.774
Hey! What's not a good idea. though.

343
00:17:47.775 --> 00:17:51.110
is trying to find Lark
and enact some kind of vigilante justice.

344
00:17:51.111 --> 00:17:54.322
I don't care about justice.
and I don't care about Lark.

345
00:17:54.323 --> 00:17:55.699
I just want my money back.

346
00:17:56.325 --> 00:17:57.700
Any idea where she is?

347
00:17:57.701 --> 00:17:59.036
No.

348
00:18:00.746 --> 00:18:03.248
No. but I think I might know
someone who does.

349
00:18:05.292 --> 00:18:06.459
Wait…

350
00:18:06.460 --> 00:18:08.920
Promise me you won't do anything stupid!

351
00:18:08.921 --> 00:18:11.924
Me? Never.

352
00:18:34.530 --> 00:18:36.240
Oh. I love you.

353
00:18:44.039 --> 00:18:45.331
Oh!

354
00:18:45.332 --> 00:18:47.834
Aloha.

355
00:18:47.835 --> 00:18:50.503
What is this?

356
00:18:50.504 --> 00:18:54.423
This is my way of saying
thank you for letting Marley move in.

357
00:18:54.424 --> 00:18:57.760
But it's not your way of trying
to convince me to go to Hawaii. clearly.

358
00:18:57.761 --> 00:19:01.222
Oh. it is also my way
of convincing you to go to Hawaii.

359
00:19:01.223 --> 00:19:03.350
Subtle.

360
00:19:04.143 --> 00:19:06.978
A virgin mai tai for my mister.

361
00:19:06.979 --> 00:19:08.939
Oh! Thank you. missus.

362
00:19:09.439 --> 00:19:10.858
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

363
00:19:14.945 --> 00:19:16.445
You know. I was thinking about it.

364
00:19:16.446 --> 00:19:19.657
and actually I think it might be a win-win
to have Marley on the farm.

365
00:19:19.658 --> 00:19:23.537
We'll have someone
to keep an eye on all our horses.

366
00:19:24.580 --> 00:19:25.581
Horses?

367
00:19:27.207 --> 00:19:29.792
I'm sorry. did Sugar multiply? Or…

368
00:19:29.793 --> 00:19:33.922
Well. Roland came by today
and gifted us two old horses.

369
00:19:35.174 --> 00:19:39.218
Well. he said it was either our place
or the proverbial glue factory. so…

370
00:19:41.054 --> 00:19:42.555
You are such a pushover.

371
00:19:42.556 --> 00:19:44.432
- I'm a pushover?
- Uh-huh.

372
00:19:44.433 --> 00:19:48.186
You're the one that said no
to adopting Marley's baby

373
00:19:48.187 --> 00:19:50.605
and ended up adopting Marley!

374
00:19:50.606 --> 00:19:52.774
At least Marley can take care of herself.

375
00:19:53.525 --> 00:19:57.486
You barely know how to take care of
one horse. let alone three.

376
00:19:57.487 --> 00:20:00.740
I just figure I'll repeat
whatever I did with Sugar two more times.

377
00:20:00.741 --> 00:20:02.701
It's just math. right?

378
00:20:03.577 --> 00:20:08.080
Or. I don't know. maybe you could
find them a home somewhere.

379
00:20:08.081 --> 00:20:10.792
On a working ranch or a farm.

380
00:20:11.376 --> 00:20:12.878
That could take a while.

381
00:20:13.587 --> 00:20:16.339
Okay. fine.
Fine. but maybe in the meantime.

382
00:20:16.340 --> 00:20:19.342
when you're figuring that out.
you can get some help.

383
00:20:19.343 --> 00:20:20.344
Yeah.

384
00:20:21.511 --> 00:20:23.137
Yeah. we're definitely gonna

385
00:20:23.138 --> 00:20:26.183
need someone to keep an eye on the place
when we're in Italy.

386
00:20:27.935 --> 00:20:31.355
Now. I think that you meant Hawaii.

387
00:20:32.564 --> 00:20:36.067
Honey. Hawaii. obviously.
Obviously Hawaii.

388
00:20:36.068 --> 00:20:37.568
But is it. though?

389
00:20:37.569 --> 00:20:38.570
Yes.

390
00:20:39.279 --> 00:20:40.656
Oh…

391
00:20:41.823 --> 00:20:44.952
<i>Che… bella donna.</i>

392
00:20:45.535 --> 00:20:46.744
What are you doing?

393
00:20:46.745 --> 00:20:49.956
Telling you you're beautiful
in the language of love.

394
00:20:49.957 --> 00:20:51.832
- Oh!
- Italian.

395
00:20:51.833 --> 00:20:53.876
Okay. then keep going.

396
00:20:53.877 --> 00:20:55.921
<i>- Vino.</i>
- Mmm!

397
00:20:56.672 --> 00:20:57.673
<i>Mangia.</i>

398
00:20:58.924 --> 00:20:59.924
Ferrari.

399
00:20:59.925 --> 00:21:02.219
- No?
- What?

400
00:21:02.886 --> 00:21:05.096
I think you should probably
quit while you're ahead.

401
00:21:05.097 --> 00:21:06.389
Oh. wait. am I ahead?

402
00:21:06.390 --> 00:21:07.807
No. you're not.

403
00:21:07.808 --> 00:21:09.101
Mmm.

404
00:21:20.570 --> 00:21:22.947
Not sure
if now's the time for spring cleaning.

405
00:21:22.948 --> 00:21:25.157
I'm looking for the town charter!

406
00:21:25.158 --> 00:21:26.993
I want to see
if there's something in there

407
00:21:26.994 --> 00:21:29.120
that can keep Grace Valley
out of our town.

408
00:21:29.121 --> 00:21:31.290
- It's worth a shot.
- Here. take that.

409
00:21:32.958 --> 00:21:33.959
This.

410
00:21:34.584 --> 00:21:36.253
- What is it?
- My father.

411
00:21:36.837 --> 00:21:40.256
Relax. he won't pop out.
He's dead. not a genie.

412
00:21:40.257 --> 00:21:41.675
I knew that.

413
00:21:42.259 --> 00:21:44.051
- Ah. here it is.
- The town charter?

414
00:21:44.052 --> 00:21:45.762
No. my mother. Catch.

415
00:21:47.097 --> 00:21:49.890
Man. you're easy to spook.

416
00:21:49.891 --> 00:21:53.436
I'm having trouble sleeping.
Baby's pressing on a nerve.

417
00:21:53.437 --> 00:21:58.190
Well. she'll be here in three weeks.
and then you can get some sleep.

418
00:21:58.191 --> 00:22:00.861
- It's not funny!
- It's a little funny.

419
00:22:01.653 --> 00:22:03.070
Don't worry.

420
00:22:03.071 --> 00:22:06.657
I'll help with the baby
while you're on "maternity leave."

421
00:22:06.658 --> 00:22:09.035
Why do you keep air-quoting
maternity leave?

422
00:22:09.036 --> 00:22:13.122
Because we'll be in the same house.
so you scratch my back…

423
00:22:13.123 --> 00:22:16.668
Once this baby comes. the only person
getting their back scratched is me.

424
00:22:17.961 --> 00:22:20.338
So. is there anything in there
that we can use?

425
00:22:20.339 --> 00:22:24.800
It's been so long since I read it.
I doubt there's anything explicit.

426
00:22:24.801 --> 00:22:28.095
Part of the reason they formed this town
was to support local business.

427
00:22:28.096 --> 00:22:33.226
because once you let a corporation in.
it's a slippery slope.

428
00:22:34.144 --> 00:22:40.733
Okay. Looks like most of my power
is over sewage and zoning.

429
00:22:40.734 --> 00:22:43.153
Glamorous thing. public service.

430
00:22:43.987 --> 00:22:45.572
Glamorous or not…

431
00:22:46.448 --> 00:22:50.202
it'd be hard for Grace Valley
to open a clinic without signs or toilets.

432
00:22:52.371 --> 00:22:53.872
Yes. it would. Lizzie.

433
00:22:54.539 --> 00:22:56.874
Set an emergency meeting
of the town council.

434
00:22:56.875 --> 00:23:01.046
We are going to get creative
and get this thing done.

435
00:23:04.591 --> 00:23:06.342
- Hey.
- Hey.

436
00:23:08.512 --> 00:23:12.181
Ooh. I am gonna miss that coffee.

437
00:23:12.182 --> 00:23:15.643
Oh. come on. now.
Your coffee isn't that bad.

438
00:23:15.644 --> 00:23:17.728
Oh. my coffee isn't even coffee.

439
00:23:17.729 --> 00:23:21.023
It's just scalding bean water
compared to yours.

440
00:23:23.443 --> 00:23:27.530
So. how was. uh…
How was your meeting with Miss Victoria?

441
00:23:27.531 --> 00:23:30.783
Oh. well. she tried to play bad cop.

442
00:23:30.784 --> 00:23:35.621
And little did she know that I was
interrogated on an episode of <i>NYPD Blue</i>.

443
00:23:35.622 --> 00:23:36.914
so I handled it.

444
00:23:36.915 --> 00:23:38.082
Ah.

445
00:23:38.083 --> 00:23:40.793
She's just in there now
with Cody and Henry.

446
00:23:40.794 --> 00:23:42.629
Well. thanks.

447
00:23:45.507 --> 00:23:48.384
I know you haven't
worked here very long. but I…

448
00:23:48.385 --> 00:23:50.678
I can't imagine this place without you.

449
00:23:50.679 --> 00:23:52.930
Well. you won't have
to imagine that for long.

450
00:23:52.931 --> 00:23:55.266
because I'm gonna be back
before you know it.

451
00:23:55.267 --> 00:23:58.811
Maybe even sooner
if my white blood cell count stays high.

452
00:23:58.812 --> 00:23:59.895
Mmm.

453
00:23:59.896 --> 00:24:03.566
I just cannot imagine
sitting around doing absolutely nothing.

454
00:24:03.567 --> 00:24:05.485
Oh. that makes two of us.

455
00:24:06.361 --> 00:24:08.904
And you're in good hands with Walt.

456
00:24:08.905 --> 00:24:11.324
He can be a… big help to you.

457
00:24:12.659 --> 00:24:14.578
Well. I still have to tell him.

458
00:24:15.370 --> 00:24:18.706
Well. he's gonna find out sooner or later.
My money is on sooner.

459
00:24:18.707 --> 00:24:22.710
Yes. I know. It's just…
enough of the people I care about

460
00:24:22.711 --> 00:24:25.254
are already looking at me
with these sad eyes.

461
00:24:25.255 --> 00:24:27.924
and I'm not ready
to see those eyes from him.

462
00:24:29.426 --> 00:24:32.679
Well. I cannot imagine
any man looking at you

463
00:24:33.346 --> 00:24:34.848
and feeling sad.

464
00:24:41.897 --> 00:24:42.898
Hey. Frank.

465
00:24:45.275 --> 00:24:47.818
Brady! Hey. man. what's up?

466
00:24:47.819 --> 00:24:49.361
- Hey.
- You okay?

467
00:24:49.362 --> 00:24:50.614
Yeah. Yeah. I'm fine.

468
00:24:51.615 --> 00:24:55.576
Uh. I'm here 'cause Lark split town.
You know where she went?

469
00:24:55.577 --> 00:24:56.494
No idea.

470
00:24:56.495 --> 00:24:58.037
I thought you two were close.

471
00:24:58.038 --> 00:25:00.498
We are.
but she doesn't tell me everything.

472
00:25:00.499 --> 00:25:03.209
She never mentioned nothing
about leaving town?

473
00:25:03.210 --> 00:25:04.586
Not that I remember.

474
00:25:06.004 --> 00:25:09.632
Hey. didn't you say
that you play cards with her mom?

475
00:25:09.633 --> 00:25:12.426
I do. but Norma doesn't talk about Lark.

476
00:25:12.427 --> 00:25:15.137
She just gets drunk and rambles.

477
00:25:15.138 --> 00:25:18.140
Last week. she was so sauced.
she spent an hour telling a story

478
00:25:18.141 --> 00:25:21.352
about how Mitch Williams cost the Phillies
the pennant in like '93--

479
00:25:21.353 --> 00:25:22.729
Okay. all right. All right.

480
00:25:23.438 --> 00:25:26.233
- So you're saying she likes to talk?
- Yeah.

481
00:25:28.068 --> 00:25:29.069
Huh.

482
00:25:38.370 --> 00:25:40.163
Hey! What's up?

483
00:25:41.498 --> 00:25:45.668
Uh. you being written up
in a major magazine is what's up.

484
00:25:45.669 --> 00:25:47.127
<i>Food & Wine!</i>

485
00:25:47.128 --> 00:25:48.505
Come on. that's huge!

486
00:25:49.422 --> 00:25:50.924
Proud of you. brother.

487
00:25:51.967 --> 00:25:54.260
I'm happy to support you however I can.

488
00:25:54.261 --> 00:25:55.928
Aw. thanks. man. For starters.

489
00:25:55.929 --> 00:25:58.639
don't give me a hard time
for handing out free drinks tonight.

490
00:25:58.640 --> 00:26:00.057
Well. why are we doing that?

491
00:26:00.058 --> 00:26:02.101
You know. pork chops.
they take a while to cook.

492
00:26:02.102 --> 00:26:05.980
and we're still getting the hang
of the other new menu items.

493
00:26:05.981 --> 00:26:07.731
- What new menu items?
- She said no!

494
00:26:09.025 --> 00:26:10.025
Hey!

495
00:26:11.987 --> 00:26:13.487
Hey! Hey! Whoa!

496
00:26:13.488 --> 00:26:16.574
- Knock it off! Hey! Hey!
- Hey. hey. hey! Hey!

497
00:26:16.575 --> 00:26:18.742
Hey. hey. hey! No fighting in my bar!

498
00:26:18.743 --> 00:26:20.911
- No. man.
- Mind your own damn business!

499
00:26:20.912 --> 00:26:24.082
Hey. man. She asked him
to leave her alone. He wouldn't listen.

500
00:26:26.209 --> 00:26:28.711
- All right. out of here!
- This is ridiculous!

501
00:26:28.712 --> 00:26:30.921
I didn't come
all the way out here for this!

502
00:26:30.922 --> 00:26:32.591
All right. show's over. folks.

503
00:26:34.467 --> 00:26:37.220
Hey. let me help you.
It's the least I can do.

504
00:26:38.096 --> 00:26:41.683
Sounds like you were defending
a woman's honor. Nothing wrong with that.

505
00:26:43.268 --> 00:26:45.394
You new in town?
I haven't seen you around.

506
00:26:45.395 --> 00:26:47.188
Yeah. I'm Clay.

507
00:26:47.772 --> 00:26:49.148
- Jack.
- Hey. man.

508
00:26:49.149 --> 00:26:51.650
I swear. I never came in here
to start a fight.

509
00:26:51.651 --> 00:26:53.360
I actually came here to look for a job.

510
00:26:53.361 --> 00:26:55.154
- Oh yeah?
- Mmm-hmm.

511
00:26:55.155 --> 00:26:58.450
- You got any restaurant experience?
- Yeah. I eat in them all the time.

512
00:26:59.159 --> 00:27:00.492
No. I've never worked in one.

513
00:27:00.493 --> 00:27:03.162
But. I mean. I got two good hands.
I'm a quick learner.

514
00:27:03.163 --> 00:27:04.956
and I'll do whatever you need me to do.

515
00:27:05.498 --> 00:27:07.541
What kind of work do you normally do?

516
00:27:07.542 --> 00:27:09.710
I spend most of my time
on the rodeo circuit.

517
00:27:09.711 --> 00:27:11.837
Ah. so you know about horses.

518
00:27:11.838 --> 00:27:13.798
I know them better than I know people.

519
00:27:14.674 --> 00:27:16.467
Yeah. I might have just the thing.

520
00:27:16.468 --> 00:27:18.761
All right. I appreciate it.

521
00:27:21.431 --> 00:27:23.932
- Hey. there.
- Hi!

522
00:27:23.933 --> 00:27:26.977
- Hey.
- I made dinner.

523
00:27:26.978 --> 00:27:28.063
Oh!

524
00:27:29.064 --> 00:27:31.316
- How was your day?
- Well…

525
00:27:32.901 --> 00:27:37.030
I'll tell you. I was not expecting
such an expedient investigation.

526
00:27:37.614 --> 00:27:39.907
Nobody expected the Spanish Inquisition.

527
00:27:39.908 --> 00:27:44.287
Mmm. Don't forget. Spain lost.
and so will Grace Valley.

528
00:27:45.372 --> 00:27:47.498
Just like Spain. that corporate hospital

529
00:27:47.499 --> 00:27:50.709
is hiding behind a philanthropic ideology.

530
00:27:50.710 --> 00:27:54.171
But all they care about is
claiming territory so they can make money.

531
00:27:54.172 --> 00:27:58.258
which means if I make it impossible
for them to do that…

532
00:27:58.259 --> 00:27:59.301
You could do that?

533
00:27:59.302 --> 00:28:01.178
With some creative new zoning laws.

534
00:28:01.179 --> 00:28:06.100
making it prohibitive for franchises
and other corporations to open in town.

535
00:28:06.101 --> 00:28:08.435
Just need the town council's approval.

536
00:28:08.436 --> 00:28:11.815
Well. I will bet they listen to you
if they know what's good for them.

537
00:28:12.732 --> 00:28:16.902
It's us against the world. Vernon.
Always has been. Always will be.

538
00:28:16.903 --> 00:28:18.154
Yeah.

539
00:28:18.905 --> 00:28:20.739
Denny and Lizzie are out.

540
00:28:20.740 --> 00:28:22.866
Ooh.

541
00:28:22.867 --> 00:28:25.494
Madam Mayor. are you seducing me?

542
00:28:25.495 --> 00:28:26.704
Not yet.

543
00:28:26.705 --> 00:28:28.123
But I'm about to.

544
00:28:28.623 --> 00:28:31.250
Ooh!

545
00:28:44.431 --> 00:28:46.725
Mmm! That smells good.

546
00:28:47.308 --> 00:28:49.351
- Hawaiian Kona coffee.
- Ooh!

547
00:28:49.352 --> 00:28:51.145
- For me?
- It's the best in the world.

548
00:28:51.146 --> 00:28:52.647
It's complex and nutty.

549
00:28:56.818 --> 00:28:58.652
Mmm-hmm?

550
00:28:58.653 --> 00:29:02.072
You're complex and nutty if you think
that's better than Italian espresso.

551
00:29:02.073 --> 00:29:03.615
- Oh. really?
- Yeah.

552
00:29:03.616 --> 00:29:06.702
Since when do you drink Italian espresso?

553
00:29:06.703 --> 00:29:08.788
I drink Italian espresso all the time.

554
00:29:09.748 --> 00:29:11.832
- This is ridiculous!
- What?

555
00:29:11.833 --> 00:29:14.168
By the time we agree
on a honeymoon destination.

556
00:29:14.169 --> 00:29:15.753
we're gonna be renewing our vows.

557
00:29:15.754 --> 00:29:17.130
We don't have to agree.

558
00:29:17.672 --> 00:29:19.632
- You're gonna give in.
- Oh yeah?

559
00:29:20.383 --> 00:29:24.136
- Mmm-hmm.
- Oh. well. we shall see about that. sir.

560
00:29:24.137 --> 00:29:25.388
Oh. we shall.

561
00:29:26.973 --> 00:29:30.642
So. you see. we can limit the signage
and architecture used

562
00:29:30.643 --> 00:29:32.603
to deter Grace Valley.

563
00:29:32.604 --> 00:29:35.814
It's not foolproof. but the more
we can do to disincentivize them

564
00:29:35.815 --> 00:29:37.649
from coming to town. the better.

565
00:29:37.650 --> 00:29:40.987
Well. shall we. uh. take this to a vote?

566
00:29:41.488 --> 00:29:43.030
That's a yes from Nick.

567
00:29:43.031 --> 00:29:45.115
No. actually. I've got a question.

568
00:29:45.116 --> 00:29:47.993
Won't these rules
keep <i>all</i> chains from coming to town?

569
00:29:47.994 --> 00:29:49.454
Ideally. yes.

570
00:29:50.121 --> 00:29:52.915
What about Jamba Juice?

571
00:29:52.916 --> 00:29:56.294
There was a rumor that they were
looking to build a store around here.

572
00:29:57.378 --> 00:29:58.420
I'm confused. Nick.

573
00:29:58.421 --> 00:30:02.841
Are you suggesting we let the clinic die
so you can have a Jamba Juice?

574
00:30:02.842 --> 00:30:08.055
I'm just suggesting that passing a law
to keep out all major corporations.

575
00:30:08.056 --> 00:30:10.265
it feels like a bridge too far.

576
00:30:10.266 --> 00:30:12.559
If you want a smoothie that bad. Nick.

577
00:30:12.560 --> 00:30:14.937
I bet the bakery truck
could start making some.

578
00:30:14.938 --> 00:30:17.064
It's not about Jamba Juice.

579
00:30:17.065 --> 00:30:19.525
It's about the idea of Jamba Juice.

580
00:30:19.526 --> 00:30:22.402
I think this town
could use a few more shops in it.

581
00:30:22.403 --> 00:30:26.073
We could. but not those kinds of shops.
They don't belong here.

582
00:30:26.074 --> 00:30:27.407
According to you!

583
00:30:27.408 --> 00:30:31.328
Why do you get to decide what kind
of shops we have in Virgin River?

584
00:30:31.329 --> 00:30:35.249
Because in case you've forgotten. Nick.
I regained my seat as mayor.

585
00:30:35.250 --> 00:30:39.212
and I think locally-owned businesses
are better for <i>my</i> town.

586
00:30:39.921 --> 00:30:41.797
Well. mayor or not.

587
00:30:41.798 --> 00:30:43.799
it's <i>our</i> town.

588
00:30:45.969 --> 00:30:48.387
I. for one. support Hope.

589
00:30:48.388 --> 00:30:52.057
because we have to do
whatever we can to protect the clinic.

590
00:30:52.058 --> 00:30:53.101
And we will!

591
00:30:54.435 --> 00:30:55.979
Just not like this.

592
00:30:57.230 --> 00:30:58.356
All opposed?

593
00:31:00.984 --> 00:31:02.569
The nays have it.

594
00:31:03.444 --> 00:31:04.696
Sorry. Hope.

595
00:31:10.451 --> 00:31:11.953
- Hey!
- Hey.

596
00:31:14.289 --> 00:31:15.289
- Hi.
- Hi.

597
00:31:15.290 --> 00:31:17.249
- You must be Clay. right?
- Yeah.

598
00:31:17.250 --> 00:31:19.334
- Hi.
- Hey. nice to meet you. ma'am.

599
00:31:19.335 --> 00:31:21.379
Uh. nice to meet you. Mel's fine.

600
00:31:22.297 --> 00:31:23.547
- Hey.
- Um. hey.

601
00:31:23.548 --> 00:31:25.591
So did you get Marley set up
in the Airstream?

602
00:31:25.592 --> 00:31:27.593
Yeah. sure did.
Clay got all her stuff loaded in.

603
00:31:27.594 --> 00:31:29.094
- Thank you.
- Not a problem.

604
00:31:29.095 --> 00:31:31.388
- You want to put them in the barn?
- Yeah. sure.

605
00:31:31.389 --> 00:31:32.681
Cheers.

606
00:31:32.682 --> 00:31:34.141
- Nice to meet you.
- You too.

607
00:31:34.142 --> 00:31:35.143
Thanks.

608
00:31:35.977 --> 00:31:38.395
So. what. you finished
at the clinic already?

609
00:31:38.396 --> 00:31:40.022
No. I just came home for lunch.

610
00:31:40.023 --> 00:31:43.483
I'm gonna help Marley go through
some profiles the agency sent over.

611
00:31:43.484 --> 00:31:46.987
But I am all yours for dinner.

612
00:31:46.988 --> 00:31:48.614
Ooh. careful how you say that.

613
00:31:48.615 --> 00:31:49.657
Oh. really?

614
00:31:50.783 --> 00:31:52.784
I was actually planning
on cooking tonight.

615
00:31:52.785 --> 00:31:56.496
Oh. something Italian. I'm assuming.
because you are relentless.

616
00:31:56.497 --> 00:31:58.874
You told me to convince you!

617
00:31:58.875 --> 00:32:00.792
Right. okay. but when I said that. I…

618
00:32:00.793 --> 00:32:04.338
What I really meant was like.
you know. "try" to convince me.

619
00:32:04.339 --> 00:32:07.299
but then fail admirably
and do whatever I want

620
00:32:07.300 --> 00:32:08.675
because you love me so much.

621
00:32:08.676 --> 00:32:11.512
Oh. you never would have
married a failure.

622
00:32:12.221 --> 00:32:14.057
Oh…

623
00:32:17.143 --> 00:32:20.562
Well. they all look like
really nice couples.

624
00:32:20.563 --> 00:32:22.982
Yeah.
well. so did Phil and Darla.

625
00:32:24.943 --> 00:32:28.947
Ah. you know. I…
I think that was just a fluke.

626
00:32:29.864 --> 00:32:31.323
- Yeah?
- I really do. I…

627
00:32:31.324 --> 00:32:33.660
Most couples that go into adoption are…

628
00:32:34.243 --> 00:32:36.329
You know. they're… they're solid.

629
00:32:37.330 --> 00:32:38.830
Like you and Jack.

630
00:32:38.831 --> 00:32:40.166
We're not perfect.

631
00:32:40.667 --> 00:32:43.335
Nobody that you choose will be.

632
00:32:43.336 --> 00:32:45.295
That's not what I thought of you

633
00:32:45.296 --> 00:32:47.381
when Phil and Darla backed out. you know?

634
00:32:47.382 --> 00:32:51.009
I didn't think that you were this perfect
person living in this perfect town.

635
00:32:51.010 --> 00:32:52.678
Well…

636
00:32:52.679 --> 00:32:55.681
I mean. I panicked.
for sure. and I was rash.

637
00:32:55.682 --> 00:32:58.141
but in the middle of that panic.

638
00:32:58.142 --> 00:33:01.020
this image of you in the rock slide
popped into my head.

639
00:33:02.230 --> 00:33:04.231
It was just this little moment.

640
00:33:04.232 --> 00:33:08.151
but when you looked me in the eyes
and told me everything was gonna be okay…

641
00:33:08.152 --> 00:33:09.278
I believed you.

642
00:33:25.837 --> 00:33:26.921
Okay.

643
00:33:27.422 --> 00:33:28.423
Mel!

644
00:33:29.257 --> 00:33:31.800
Mel. she's hemorrhaging.
We need to get this baby delivered.

645
00:33:31.801 --> 00:33:34.344
No. I know.
but she won't push anymore. Eli.

646
00:33:34.345 --> 00:33:36.221
- She's terrified! I don't--
- It's okay.

647
00:33:36.222 --> 00:33:41.310
Listen. I want you to look into her eyes
and make her believe she's gonna be okay.

648
00:33:46.065 --> 00:33:47.817
Is she gonna be okay?

649
00:33:48.401 --> 00:33:51.070
She will be if you make her believe it.

650
00:33:52.822 --> 00:33:55.032
I know you can do this.
Take a deep breath.

651
00:33:56.034 --> 00:33:57.160
Yeah. Good.

652
00:33:58.077 --> 00:33:59.494
- It's gonna be okay.
- Okay.

653
00:33:59.495 --> 00:34:00.787
Be strong for her.

654
00:34:00.788 --> 00:34:01.914
- Okay.
- Okay.

655
00:34:03.207 --> 00:34:05.626
- Okay.
- Here. let me help you sit up.

656
00:34:07.503 --> 00:34:09.380
Hey. Hey.

657
00:34:10.089 --> 00:34:11.132
It's okay.

658
00:34:13.634 --> 00:34:14.719
You're okay.

659
00:34:16.012 --> 00:34:17.805
Thank you for saying that.

660
00:34:34.697 --> 00:34:35.865
- Hey.
- Hey.

661
00:34:37.700 --> 00:34:38.826
Can I come in?

662
00:34:39.327 --> 00:34:40.661
Yeah. of course.

663
00:34:45.416 --> 00:34:46.417
Uh…

664
00:34:49.754 --> 00:34:50.921
How are you?

665
00:34:50.922 --> 00:34:53.007
Um. I don't know.

666
00:34:53.508 --> 00:34:55.717
Between Calvin's murder investigation.

667
00:34:55.718 --> 00:34:58.679
Charmaine's missing persons case.
and my girlfriend

668
00:34:59.555 --> 00:35:02.974
leaving me hanging on my
marriage proposal. yeah. it's been better.

669
00:35:02.975 --> 00:35:05.561
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I…

670
00:35:06.437 --> 00:35:07.979
just needed to think.

671
00:35:07.980 --> 00:35:12.777
Uh-huh. Do you want to… at least tell me
what you've been thinking about?

672
00:35:13.945 --> 00:35:15.696
I've just been thinking about.

673
00:35:16.197 --> 00:35:21.369
you know. how realistic it is
for either of us to move past this.

674
00:35:22.578 --> 00:35:26.165
- Like. I know <i>you</i> said you can.
- Yeah. and… hey…

675
00:35:26.999 --> 00:35:28.750
I meant it. okay?

676
00:35:28.751 --> 00:35:31.378
I love you. and the only thing
that you need to think about

677
00:35:31.379 --> 00:35:33.713
is if you love me enough to commit to us.

678
00:35:33.714 --> 00:35:36.592
And we can…
we can have a beautiful life together.

679
00:35:37.176 --> 00:35:38.219
I know.

680
00:35:39.303 --> 00:35:43.057
I know. It would be a… dream.

681
00:35:47.395 --> 00:35:49.021
- But…
- But you don't want the dream.

682
00:35:49.856 --> 00:35:51.482
Or you don't want it with <i>me</i>.

683
00:35:52.316 --> 00:35:53.650
All right. don't…

684
00:35:53.651 --> 00:35:54.652
don't…

685
00:35:56.404 --> 00:35:58.029
Don't do that. please.

686
00:35:58.030 --> 00:35:59.614
Don't make this about Brady.

687
00:35:59.615 --> 00:36:02.784
It is always about Brady.

688
00:36:02.785 --> 00:36:06.788
The night of my promotion.
it was about Brady.

689
00:36:06.789 --> 00:36:08.290
What are you talking about?

690
00:36:08.291 --> 00:36:12.627
Are you kidding me?
I could sense the tension between you two.

691
00:36:12.628 --> 00:36:15.046
and then you randomly asked me to move in.

692
00:36:15.047 --> 00:36:16.423
Is that how you knew?

693
00:36:16.424 --> 00:36:20.677
- You must think I'm some kind of idiot.
- I swear. Mike. this is not about him.

694
00:36:20.678 --> 00:36:23.847
Then why. huh?
Why are you blowing this up?

695
00:36:23.848 --> 00:36:26.099
Because no matter
how hard I try.

696
00:36:26.100 --> 00:36:28.852
and no matter how much
I do want to be with you.

697
00:36:28.853 --> 00:36:31.938
for some reason. I just can't get there
with my whole heart.

698
00:36:31.939 --> 00:36:35.026
and I don't know how to tell you
that I never will.

699
00:36:39.113 --> 00:36:40.323
You just did.

700
00:36:41.407 --> 00:36:43.201
- Mike…
- We're done.

701
00:36:48.831 --> 00:36:52.919
I'm not so sure about this. Brady.
I have a terrible poker face.

702
00:36:53.628 --> 00:36:56.797
Come on. Frank.
Aren't you taking me <i>to</i> a poker game?

703
00:37:06.474 --> 00:37:09.142
- Hey. everybody.
- Who's the looker. Frank?

704
00:37:09.143 --> 00:37:11.770
Uh. this is my friend…

705
00:37:11.771 --> 00:37:14.231
Brian… uh. from Barstow.

706
00:37:14.232 --> 00:37:17.651
Uh. he's in town for a few days.
and he's looking to have some fun.

707
00:37:17.652 --> 00:37:22.657
I. uh. I hope it's okay.
I brought <i>my</i> friend Jim with me.

708
00:37:23.699 --> 00:37:26.117
Pour me a shot. She'll deal you in.

709
00:37:26.118 --> 00:37:27.828
My pleasure.

710
00:37:35.086 --> 00:37:37.295
What did that burger do to you?

711
00:37:37.296 --> 00:37:39.590
Lay off. I'm eating for two.

712
00:37:42.510 --> 00:37:44.886
So. has Nick always been
such a huge pain in the butt?

713
00:37:44.887 --> 00:37:46.389
He used to be worse.

714
00:37:47.306 --> 00:37:49.558
I don't know how
Jo Ellen tolerates that man.

715
00:37:51.018 --> 00:37:53.687
Well. you might not
be able to change his mind. but…

716
00:37:53.688 --> 00:37:57.358
if we stay at it. you might be able
to swing enough votes to overrule him.

717
00:37:57.942 --> 00:37:59.026
Mmm.

718
00:38:00.820 --> 00:38:03.197
Cody. your order might be ready.
I'll go check.

719
00:38:07.994 --> 00:38:09.327
Hi. Cody.

720
00:38:09.328 --> 00:38:10.537
Hey.

721
00:38:10.538 --> 00:38:12.790
I'm so glad your dad's on the mend.

722
00:38:13.916 --> 00:38:17.210
Uh. Dr. Mullins and I really appreciate
you going to bat for him

723
00:38:17.211 --> 00:38:19.129
with that awful investigator.

724
00:38:19.130 --> 00:38:20.339
Oh. um…

725
00:38:20.840 --> 00:38:23.383
She's just trying to make sure
people follow the rules.

726
00:38:23.384 --> 00:38:25.928
Which is exactly what Dr. Mullins did.

727
00:38:27.638 --> 00:38:30.098
Yeah. well. I don't know.

728
00:38:30.099 --> 00:38:33.351
I guess it seems pretty crazy
for Doc's license to get suspended

729
00:38:33.352 --> 00:38:35.479
if he didn't do anything wrong.

730
00:38:36.063 --> 00:38:38.273
But you were there. in the room.

731
00:38:38.274 --> 00:38:41.569
Well. I wanted to be.
but Doc told me to leave.

732
00:38:42.111 --> 00:38:43.404
so I have no idea.

733
00:38:44.196 --> 00:38:48.159
I mean. don't get me wrong.
I'm grateful Doc saved my dad's life. but…

734
00:38:49.952 --> 00:38:51.578
maybe he got lucky.

735
00:38:51.579 --> 00:38:54.664
If he hadn't been.
who knows what could've happened.

736
00:38:54.665 --> 00:38:57.251
Here you go.

737
00:38:58.836 --> 00:39:02.213
Thank you. Sorry. Mayor. I gotta go.

738
00:39:02.214 --> 00:39:03.632
Yeah. bye.

739
00:39:11.682 --> 00:39:14.267
Hannah. how many pork chops
are you able to brine?

740
00:39:14.268 --> 00:39:15.519
Two dozen. chef.

741
00:39:16.479 --> 00:39:17.562
- Oh…
- Hey. whoa.

742
00:39:17.563 --> 00:39:18.855
Whoa. you okay?

743
00:39:18.856 --> 00:39:20.358
Yeah. I just have PTSD.

744
00:39:21.192 --> 00:39:24.235
Pork Traumatic Stress Disorder
from the rehearsal dinner.

745
00:39:24.236 --> 00:39:26.529
- I'll survive!
- Well. good to know.

746
00:39:26.530 --> 00:39:28.657
Hey. do you. uh…

747
00:39:32.828 --> 00:39:33.870
Hey. you.

748
00:39:33.871 --> 00:39:35.246
Where are you?

749
00:39:35.247 --> 00:39:37.248
<i>Oh. I'm still at the bar.</i>

750
00:39:37.249 --> 00:39:40.001
I thought you were gonna come home
between lunch and dinner service.

751
00:39:40.002 --> 00:39:41.252
Yeah. I was planning to.

752
00:39:41.253 --> 00:39:45.091
but these pork chops are proving to be
a very complicated addition to the menu.

753
00:39:45.925 --> 00:39:49.220
Uh. okay.
Um. I guess I'll see you later. then?

754
00:39:49.845 --> 00:39:51.930
You know. I. uh… No. I wouldn't wait up.

755
00:39:51.931 --> 00:39:54.140
We got a lot of pork to prep for tomorrow.

756
00:39:54.141 --> 00:39:56.059
<i>but I will see you
first thing in the morning</i>

757
00:39:56.060 --> 00:39:58.270
<i>with a hot cup of</i> café de olla.

758
00:39:59.021 --> 00:40:00.022
Love you.

759
00:40:00.523 --> 00:40:01.689
<i>Love you.</i>

760
00:40:22.545 --> 00:40:25.004
- Here's your spritz.
- Oh. thank you.

761
00:40:25.005 --> 00:40:26.340
- You're welcome.
- Hmm.

762
00:40:27.133 --> 00:40:30.886
You know. some call that
the mai tai of Italy.

763
00:40:31.512 --> 00:40:34.556
Oh my gosh. Well. it's delicious.

764
00:40:34.557 --> 00:40:37.518
Oh. good. I got another surprise for you.

765
00:40:38.102 --> 00:40:40.270
Better not be a Fiat.

766
00:40:42.314 --> 00:40:44.567
It's not.

767
00:40:45.526 --> 00:40:47.069
Ah-ah-ah!

768
00:40:49.864 --> 00:40:51.114
Oh my goodness!

769
00:40:51.115 --> 00:40:53.533
- Is that a Hawaiian pizza?
- I don't know.

770
00:40:53.534 --> 00:40:56.619
I'm not even sure this is actually pizza.
whatever I've made here. but…

771
00:40:56.620 --> 00:40:57.997
It looks like pizza.

772
00:40:58.581 --> 00:41:00.331
- You know what it is?
- Hmm.

773
00:41:00.332 --> 00:41:02.292
It's a gesture of compromise.

774
00:41:02.293 --> 00:41:05.462
So. are you saying
we can go to both places?

775
00:41:05.463 --> 00:41:07.423
- Ha-ha-ha!
- Hmm?

776
00:41:08.424 --> 00:41:14.221
All I'm saying is. it doesn't matter to me
where we go. because every day with you…

777
00:41:15.389 --> 00:41:16.724
will be a honeymoon.

778
00:41:17.766 --> 00:41:19.017
Aww.

779
00:41:19.018 --> 00:41:20.936
That's very sweet.

780
00:41:23.230 --> 00:41:24.189
Well…

781
00:41:24.190 --> 00:41:30.445
Um. but we might want to postpone that
for maybe a little bit longer.

782
00:41:30.446 --> 00:41:31.696
Uh. okay.

783
00:41:31.697 --> 00:41:34.408
- Why?
- I was thinking

784
00:41:35.075 --> 00:41:39.121
that maybe we should reconsider
adopting Marley's baby.

785
00:41:42.041 --> 00:41:43.459
Okay! Well…

786
00:41:44.210 --> 00:41:45.752
what made you change your mind?

787
00:41:45.753 --> 00:41:51.883
Well. uh. she was…
telling me that at the rock slide. she…

788
00:41:51.884 --> 00:41:57.055
she saw this strength in me.
even when I don't know what's coming next.

789
00:41:57.056 --> 00:42:01.267
That's a quality that she wants
in the mother of her child.

790
00:42:01.268 --> 00:42:04.479
And it just…
It really meant a lot to me because it's…

791
00:42:04.480 --> 00:42:07.441
it's the part of myself
that I'm the most proud of.

792
00:42:08.442 --> 00:42:11.070
You know. it's one of the reasons
I fell in love with you.

793
00:42:12.613 --> 00:42:13.614
Oh.

794
00:42:14.240 --> 00:42:16.700
It sounds like she's thought this through.

795
00:42:17.243 --> 00:42:20.078
- Yeah. That's what I thought too. yeah.
- Right?

796
00:42:20.079 --> 00:42:22.248
So. what do you think?

797
00:42:23.457 --> 00:42:26.793
I mean. we both agreed
that the right baby would find us. right?

798
00:42:26.794 --> 00:42:27.795
Mmm-hmm.

799
00:42:29.630 --> 00:42:33.550
So I don't want to turn our back on that
just 'cause having a baby right now isn't…

800
00:42:33.551 --> 00:42:34.759
part of the plan.

801
00:42:34.760 --> 00:42:36.010
I know.

802
00:42:36.011 --> 00:42:39.390
I know! I think I was just…
I was being protective. and…

803
00:42:40.307 --> 00:42:44.979
But it does feel really good
knowing that it's coming now.

804
00:42:47.022 --> 00:42:50.067
I mean. it's like almost
too good to be true.

805
00:42:50.568 --> 00:42:51.694
Hey…

806
00:42:52.236 --> 00:42:54.113
I think we're due for a blessing.

807
00:42:54.905 --> 00:42:56.990
Yeah. We are.

808
00:42:58.158 --> 00:43:00.244
I think we should do it.

809
00:43:00.869 --> 00:43:01.870
'Kay.

810
00:43:18.721 --> 00:43:20.764
Wow. I am sorry. man.

811
00:43:21.265 --> 00:43:22.850
I cannot believe Brady.

812
00:43:23.350 --> 00:43:27.146
She said that her turning me down
wasn't about him.

813
00:43:27.646 --> 00:43:28.647
Which kinda made it worse.

814
00:43:30.441 --> 00:43:32.150
You gonna be all right?

815
00:43:32.151 --> 00:43:36.404
It feels like a lot
with Charmaine and her twins missing.

816
00:43:36.405 --> 00:43:37.905
and with all of this.

817
00:43:37.906 --> 00:43:41.409
The case is keeping my mind busy.
which isn't such a bad thing.

818
00:43:41.410 --> 00:43:43.036
Charmaine. she must be terrified.

819
00:43:43.037 --> 00:43:48.082
I have seen firsthand how one bad man
can send a woman's whole life sideways.

820
00:43:48.083 --> 00:43:50.252
If she did do it.

821
00:43:50.878 --> 00:43:52.962
it had to have been self-defense.

822
00:43:52.963 --> 00:43:54.256
Yeah. but why would she run?

823
00:43:54.840 --> 00:43:56.383
Maybe she got spooked.

824
00:43:57.301 --> 00:43:59.970
Or someone spooked <i>her</i>.

825
00:44:01.013 --> 00:44:03.182
A lot of people wanted Calvin dead.

826
00:44:03.932 --> 00:44:05.517
But at her house?

827
00:44:06.185 --> 00:44:07.478
Who would do that?

828
00:44:08.687 --> 00:44:09.688
And why?

829
00:44:57.945 --> 00:44:59.113
Hey. Jack.

830
00:45:00.155 --> 00:45:02.908
No. I'm not busy. Just grazing the horses.

831
00:45:03.784 --> 00:45:04.827
Mmm-hmm.

832
00:45:05.703 --> 00:45:07.079
Yeah. I'll get right on it.

833
00:45:13.043 --> 00:45:15.169
- Good morning.
- Hi. baby.

834
00:45:15.170 --> 00:45:17.880
Hey. I didn't want to wake you
last night 'cause. uh…

835
00:45:17.881 --> 00:45:21.008
Denny and I stayed late
at the clinic studying for the MCAT.

836
00:45:21.009 --> 00:45:23.886
- Mmm.
- So. how did the town council go?

837
00:45:23.887 --> 00:45:25.596
It… went.

838
00:45:25.597 --> 00:45:28.266
Um. I still have some work to do
to get enough votes

839
00:45:28.267 --> 00:45:32.228
to pass my zoning ordinance. but Lizzie
and I are confident we'll get it done.

840
00:45:32.229 --> 00:45:36.275
Well. seems like maybe the investigation's
turning in our direction too.

841
00:45:37.151 --> 00:45:39.736
- Yeah. about that--
- I'm sorry to interrupt.

842
00:45:39.737 --> 00:45:41.821
Please. by all means. interrupt.

843
00:45:41.822 --> 00:45:43.741
Okay! Well…

844
00:45:44.867 --> 00:45:45.950
I'm in labor!

845
00:45:45.951 --> 00:45:48.202
- Labor?
- You're in labor?

846
00:45:48.203 --> 00:45:51.331
- What do you mean you're in labor?
- I'm having a baby!

846
00:45:52.305 --> 00:46:52.650
